- l hate you!

504
00:29:14,996 --> 00:29:16,258
Anya, listen to me.

505
00:29:16,330 --> 00:29:18,264
That producer was going
to sign with me today.

506
00:29:18,332 --> 00:29:20,800
He would have signed you,
but where was the contract?

507
00:29:21,002 --> 00:29:22,902
ln the hotel room of
that drunkard producer?

508
00:29:22,970 --> 00:29:25,803
For your information, the
contract was in his pocket.

509
00:29:25,873 --> 00:29:27,670
The pen was in his hotel room.

510
00:29:28,009 --> 00:29:32,673
Anya, acting is just nonsense.

511
00:29:33,448 --> 00:29:37,714
Acting is like..
is like chewing gum.

512
00:29:38,519 --> 00:29:40,953
lt feels good to
chew in the beginning.

513
00:29:40,988 --> 00:29:43,718
Later on, it gets
difficult to spit it out.

514
00:29:44,258 --> 00:29:45,987
You've been chewing
it for a long time.

515
00:29:46,260 --> 00:29:48,524
That's why you get
emotionally attached.

516
00:29:49,497 --> 00:29:51,488
Forget about acting, darling.

517
00:29:52,333 --> 00:29:56,326
At least l'm trying to lead an
honest and respectable life.

518
00:29:56,637 --> 00:29:59,663
Being an item girl is a million
times better than being a thief.

519
00:30:01,442 --> 00:30:03,501
Zip. l'm not a thief.

520
00:30:03,578 --> 00:30:08,481
l'm a con-artist. A crime artist.

521
00:30:08,683 --> 00:30:11,481
Secondly, mother will hear.
Lower your voice.

522
00:30:11,519 --> 00:30:12,679
Let her hear!

523
00:30:13,521 --> 00:30:17,685
Let mother also know that her son,
who is the apple of her eye..

524
00:30:17,792 --> 00:30:20,590
..who she thinks is
a big film director..

525
00:30:20,628 --> 00:30:24,621
..is none other than the
wanted criminal Tees Maar Khan.

526
00:30:27,401 --> 00:30:31,701
No! Wanted criminal Tees Maar Khan?

527
00:30:31,772 --> 00:30:33,569
Where? Where is he?

528
00:30:35,510 --> 00:30:38,775
Did you see that? Tees Maar Khan
is not a criminal, Mother.

529
00:30:38,846 --> 00:30:41,644
lt's the name of my next film.

530
00:30:41,716 --> 00:30:42,808
Oh, God!
- Silly.

531
00:30:42,884 --> 00:30:43,942
What do you think?

532
00:30:44,018 --> 00:30:47,886
Very good. Better than
your last film.

533
00:30:47,955 --> 00:30:49,081
Which film?

534
00:30:49,357 --> 00:30:51,325
Well, 'Om Shanti Om'.

535
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:55,923
Sharp memory. You've
been feasting on almonds.

536
00:30:55,997 --> 00:30:57,726
Well, that's enough.
Sit down. Sit here.

537
00:30:57,798 --> 00:30:59,493
Anya, come here, dear.

538
00:30:59,534 --> 00:31:00,626
Come. Come.

539
00:31:01,569 --> 00:31:03,537
You've come after a long time.

540
00:31:03,638 --> 00:31:06,937
So l've prepared 'shikh kebab'
(lndian dish) for both of you.

541
00:31:07,008 --> 00:31:08,635
Both of you have it, okay?
- Okay.

542
00:31:08,709 --> 00:31:11,007
Till then l'll prepare 'biryani'.
- Okay, Mother.

543
00:31:14,749 --> 00:31:15,977
Why do you shout so much?

544
00:31:16,684 --> 00:31:18,276
You and your tonsils.

545
00:31:18,352 --> 00:31:19,876
What if mother would have found out?

546
00:31:20,454 --> 00:31:22,319
So what if she had found out?

547
00:31:22,557 --> 00:31:24,548
lt would've broken mother's heart.

548
00:31:24,892 --> 00:31:26,450
And your bones as well.

549
00:31:26,961 --> 00:31:30,920
lt's so shameful that
your mother doesn't know..

550
00:31:30,998 --> 00:31:32,522
..that you aren't a film director..

551
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:34,591
..but the wanted
criminal Tees Maar Khan.

552
00:31:35,536 --> 00:31:37,731
That's nothing new, you idiot.

553
00:31:38,072 --> 00:31:41,303
Even Spiderman's mother
doesn't know that he's Spiderman.

554
00:31:41,375 --> 00:31:42,467
So what?

555
00:31:42,677 --> 00:31:47,910
At least l can say that l'm
the beauty queen Anya Khan.

556
00:31:48,416 --> 00:31:51,351
Do you have the guts to tell
the world who you really are?

557
00:31:51,419 --> 00:31:53,819
That you're Tees Maar Khan?
Chicken.

558
00:31:54,355 --> 00:31:56,084
Me?
- Yes, you are.

559
00:31:56,457 --> 00:31:58,948
l'll show you whether l'm a
chicken or a brave man. Wait.

560
00:31:59,894 --> 00:32:03,921
Yes! l am Tees Maar Khan!
l am Tees Maar Khan!

561
00:32:06,968 --> 00:32:09,835
Boss, the police!

562
00:32:10,404 --> 00:32:11,871
l'm not Tees Maar Khan.

563
00:32:11,939 --> 00:32:14,999
l swear by Allah, l'm not.
l'm not. l swear.

564
00:32:18,379 --> 00:32:20,540
The police are outside. Handle them.
- Police?

565
00:32:23,050 --> 00:32:24,278
And mother too.

566
00:32:24,385 --> 00:32:25,977
But Tabrez, how can l?

567
00:32:26,020 --> 00:32:27,851
You desire to be an actress,
don't you? - Yes.

568
00:32:27,955 --> 00:32:29,354
Go do your acting. Go on.

569
00:32:36,530 --> 00:32:38,464
Who is it? Has anyone died?

570
00:32:38,532 --> 00:32:39,760
Who is ringing the bell repeatedly?

571
00:32:39,834 --> 00:32:42,803
Mummy, two actors were supposed
to come for the screen test.

572
00:32:42,970 --> 00:32:44,028
Actors?

573
00:32:44,405 --> 00:32:45,770
For 'Tees Maar Khan'.

574
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:47,068
They were called for
the role of cops.

575
00:32:47,341 --> 00:32:49,673
Oh, yes. But where is Tabrez?

576
00:32:49,744 --> 00:32:50,836
Where is he?

577
00:32:50,911 --> 00:32:52,378
He's hiding.

578
00:32:52,647 --> 00:32:54,080
He's hiding? But why?

579
00:32:54,815 --> 00:32:56,680
They have to act as if
they're searching for him.

580
00:32:56,751 --> 00:32:57,843
That's the test.

581
00:32:59,553 --> 00:33:02,716
So let's do one thing.
l'll take their test.

582
00:33:02,890 --> 00:33:05,415
After all,
l'm the director's mother.

583
00:33:05,459 --> 00:33:07,586
Do one thing. Go sit over there.

584
00:33:08,262 --> 00:33:09,354
Okay.

585
00:33:11,932 --> 00:33:13,559
Police.
- ls Tees Maar Khan here?

586
00:33:13,634 --> 00:33:14,999
You idiots!

587
00:33:15,503 --> 00:33:17,733
Are you cops or people
who ask for donations?

588
00:33:17,805 --> 00:33:21,764
You'll ask me where Tees
Maar Khan is and l'll tell you?

589
00:33:21,842 --> 00:33:23,776
Come on. Ask me again. Again.

590
00:33:23,844 --> 00:33:26,369
And this time ask me a bit strictly.
Okay? - Yes. Yes.

591
00:33:26,514 --> 00:33:27,776
Come on.

592
00:33:34,488 --> 00:33:36,513
Police!
- ls Tees Maar Khan here?

593
00:33:36,557 --> 00:33:37,785
That's more like it.

594
00:33:37,992 --> 00:33:40,859
Now you push me and enter.

595
00:33:41,429 --> 00:33:43,420
Come on, push me. Get in the house.

596
00:33:46,367 --> 00:33:47,629
l pushed you.

597
00:33:47,802 --> 00:33:50,032
You too. Push me. Come on.

598
00:33:50,404 --> 00:33:52,964
Where do these people come from?

599
00:33:53,774 --> 00:33:55,071
Brother, he said he
must be here somewhere.

600
00:33:55,343 --> 00:33:56,605
Mummy!
- What happened?

601
00:33:56,677 --> 00:33:57,769
l'll search for proof here.
You look there.

602
00:33:57,845 --> 00:33:58,971
Oh, Allah!

603
00:33:59,313 --> 00:34:02,612
You idiot, you did get
into the character..

604
00:34:02,683 --> 00:34:05,652
..but who will clean up
the mess you've created?

605
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:07,278
Your father?

606
00:34:07,355 --> 00:34:09,755
Come on. Put it inside.
Put everything back.

607
00:34:09,824 --> 00:34:11,485
No. No. Why will he do that?
Tell me.

608
00:34:11,559 --> 00:34:13,789
Not just him. You too will
put everything back. Okay?

609
00:34:13,861 --> 00:34:14,987
l'll also do it.

610
00:34:16,263 --> 00:34:17,696
Will you put it back
or should l slap you?

611
00:34:17,765 --> 00:34:19,858
Run. Run.
- The old lady has gone mad.

612
00:34:19,934 --> 00:34:21,333
Run.

613
00:34:21,402 --> 00:34:22,494
Move!
- Get in.

614
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:27,398
Boss.

615
00:34:28,843 --> 00:34:32,472
The Khan of Khans..
- Tees Maar Khan.

616
00:34:33,748 --> 00:34:34,942
Boss..
- You scoundrel.

617
00:34:35,015 --> 00:34:36,312
That reminds me.

618
00:34:36,384 --> 00:34:37,510
There was a call for you
from the Johri Brothers.

619
00:34:37,551 --> 00:34:39,519
Johri Brothers? The
international antique smugglers?

620
00:34:39,587 --> 00:34:40,713
What do they have to do with boss?

621
00:34:40,788 --> 00:34:42,915
ln just a couple of minutes, you
guys and l will know everything.

622
00:34:42,990 --> 00:34:44,855
Phone.
- Sir. - Good.

623
00:34:44,925 --> 00:34:47,553
Mother has the same handset model.

624
00:34:49,363 --> 00:34:50,591
Mother's photograph?

625
00:34:50,798 --> 00:34:53,426
Rascal, you stole my mother's phone.
- Sorry.

626
00:34:53,634 --> 00:34:57,502
l like robbers. l like robbers.
l like robbers.

627
00:34:58,472 --> 00:34:59,530
Hello.

628
00:35:00,574 --> 00:35:05,978
The pigeon is out of the cage.
lt's ready to pick up the food.

629
00:35:06,247 --> 00:35:08,943
From when and where the
food needs to be picked up..

630
00:35:09,417 --> 00:35:10,543
..you'll tell me that.

631
00:35:10,818 --> 00:35:11,978
Putting it on speakerphone.

632
00:35:12,253 --> 00:35:14,551
Tomorrow night.
'Dandiya' (lndian dance form).

633
00:35:15,623 --> 00:35:16,715
Okay.

634
00:35:16,757 --> 00:35:18,691
'Dandiya!'

635
00:35:20,461 --> 00:35:22,395
''This is the night to celebrate.''

636
00:35:22,463 --> 00:35:24,055
''And l have your company.''

637
00:35:24,165 --> 00:35:27,623
''Today l have your hand in my hand.''

638
00:35:27,701 --> 00:35:29,635
''This is the night to celebrate.''

639
00:35:29,703 --> 00:35:31,534
''And l have your company.''

640
00:35:31,605 --> 00:35:34,972
''Today l have your hand in my hand.''

641
00:35:41,882 --> 00:35:43,042
There are the Siamese twins.

642
00:35:43,317 --> 00:35:44,511
Boss, your stick.

643
00:35:44,585 --> 00:35:45,643
Thank you.

644
00:35:45,719 --> 00:35:47,050
'Dandiya!'
- Rascal!

645
00:35:47,388 --> 00:35:48,650
Come, Tees Maar Khan.

646
00:35:48,722 --> 00:35:51,486
You probably know why
we've called you here.

647
00:35:51,692 --> 00:35:53,592
You've called me to play 'Dandiya'..

648
00:35:53,627 --> 00:35:54,889
..on the occasion of
'Dusshera' (lndian festival).

649
00:35:54,995 --> 00:35:56,485
Bad joke. Should we laugh?

650
00:35:56,564 --> 00:35:59,795
lf you guys want to get
your Rs.5 billion antiques..

651
00:35:59,867 --> 00:36:03,826
..from the police, then you'll
have to laugh at my lousy joke.

652
00:36:05,539 --> 00:36:08,633
Then you might also know that
only one man can do this job.

653
00:36:08,709 --> 00:36:09,801
l know.

654
00:36:10,344 --> 00:36:13,711
And that is the Khan of Khans..
- Tees Maar Khan!

655
00:36:13,781 --> 00:36:15,442
That means you'll do this job.

656
00:36:15,483 --> 00:36:16,950
Are you asking me or telling me?

657
00:36:17,017 --> 00:36:18,382
We're asking you.

658
00:36:18,452 --> 00:36:20,283
All right. Then l'll do it.

659
00:36:22,423 --> 00:36:25,620
Now the deal. 50 percent of
the value of the goods is for me.

660
00:36:27,261 --> 00:36:29,525
That was not a joke, you rascals.

661
00:36:29,597 --> 00:36:30,655
Blackmail?

662
00:36:30,731 --> 00:36:33,359
Those goods belong to us.
You just have to get it out.

663
00:36:34,935 --> 00:36:36,368
Goods weighing 10,000kg.

664
00:36:36,403 --> 00:36:37,927
l have to get it out
of a moving train.

665
00:36:37,972 --> 00:36:39,337
Moreover, it's in the
possession of the police.

666
00:36:39,373 --> 00:36:40,465
Do you think it's child's play?

667
00:36:40,708 --> 00:36:45,509
But if l don't do your job,
then you'll lose your treasure.

668
00:36:45,546 --> 00:36:47,605
Ladies and gentlemen.

669
00:36:47,681 --> 00:36:48,841
There. There.

670
00:36:48,916 --> 00:36:50,474
What happened?

671
00:36:50,518 --> 00:36:53,282
Please welcome our
chief guest for today..

672
00:36:53,354 --> 00:36:56,346
..superstar Aatish Kapoor.
- Here!

673
00:36:56,423 --> 00:36:59,290
Aatish!

674
00:36:59,360 --> 00:37:01,954
Aatish!

675
00:37:02,229 --> 00:37:04,720
Aatish!

676
00:37:04,798 --> 00:37:07,266
Aatish!

677
00:37:07,334 --> 00:37:09,802
Aatish!

678
00:37:09,870 --> 00:37:12,600
Aatish! Aatish Kapoor, l love you.

679
00:37:12,673 --> 00:37:13,765
What are you doing here?

680
00:37:13,807 --> 00:37:15,365
l've come to see Aatish Kapoor.

681
00:37:15,409 --> 00:37:17,309
l'm a big fan of his.

682
00:37:17,411 --> 00:37:18,969
You go home.
- Aatish, l love you!

683
00:37:19,246 --> 00:37:20,338
Otherwise l'll kill you.

684
00:37:20,414 --> 00:37:21,779
Come on. Over there.

685
00:37:21,849 --> 00:37:23,441
You're so mean.
- Yes, l'm mean.

686
00:37:23,484 --> 00:37:26,317
Now superstar Aatish Kapoor
will give away the trophy..

687
00:37:26,387 --> 00:37:27,877
..to Dollar Club
best 'Dandiya' couple.

688
00:37:27,955 --> 00:37:29,616
Give him a big hand.

689
00:37:29,823 --> 00:37:31,313
l won't take less than 50 percent.

690
00:37:31,392 --> 00:37:32,791
l said 50. Only 50.

691
00:37:33,327 --> 00:37:37,855
And Dollar Club best
'Dandiya' couple trophy goes to..

692
00:37:39,967 --> 00:37:41,696
..my friend over there.

693
00:37:41,769 --> 00:37:43,031
l said 50 percent. Nothing less.

694
00:37:43,304 --> 00:37:44,635
Boss! Boss!

695
00:37:44,705 --> 00:37:46,036
Party! Party!

696
00:37:47,274 --> 00:37:49,799
Brother, Johri Brothers.
- Tees Maar Khan.

697
00:37:49,877 --> 00:37:52,437
Catch them!
- Boss, police!

698
00:37:52,513 --> 00:37:55,414
Catch them! Catch them!

699
00:37:55,482 --> 00:37:57,450
There's still time.
Tell me quickly. 50 percent.

700
00:37:57,551 --> 00:37:58,575
The cops are coming.

701
00:37:58,619 --> 00:37:59,745
Done!
- Done!

702
00:37:59,820 --> 00:38:00,787
Open the ATM.

703
00:38:00,888 --> 00:38:02,753
Deduct it from my share.

704
00:38:02,823 --> 00:38:05,656
Take it! Take it!

705
00:38:05,826 --> 00:38:08,454
Got away, boss.
- Yes!

706
00:38:09,330 --> 00:38:11,890
Stop. Let's go.

707
00:38:11,966 --> 00:38:14,526
Sir, sir, you do the honors.
- Sir.

708
00:38:15,235 --> 00:38:17,533
Come here. Come here.

709
00:38:25,746 --> 00:38:29,648
l don't know how l'm
going to do this job.

710
00:38:30,818 --> 00:38:34,379
This is the toughest
assignment yet.

711
00:38:34,455 --> 00:38:35,547
What's so difficult, boss?

712
00:38:35,623 --> 00:38:37,454
Add these spices to the chicken.

713
00:38:37,524 --> 00:38:38,855
..then add the chicken to the curd..

714
00:38:38,959 --> 00:38:41,757
Don't you know that
boss' mind works overtime..

715
00:38:41,795 --> 00:38:43,524
..while preparing food?

716
00:38:43,564 --> 00:38:44,656
Sorry, boss.

717
00:38:45,499 --> 00:38:48,900
Getting 10,000kg of
antiques from a moving train..

718
00:38:48,969 --> 00:38:52,405
..and that train might
have around 20 to 30 cops.

719
00:38:52,473 --> 00:38:54,634
Boss, we might trick the cops.

720
00:38:54,808 --> 00:38:57,868
But how are we going to
carry stuff weighing 10,000kg?

721
00:38:57,945 --> 00:38:59,276
lt will take at least a month.

722
00:38:59,613 --> 00:39:00,910
Moreover, we'll have to go to
the hospital a couple of times..

723
00:39:00,981 --> 00:39:02,414
..to get our broken backs treated.

724
00:39:02,616 --> 00:39:04,447
Boss, we'll need more men.

725
00:39:04,485 --> 00:39:07,215
We'll need 200 to 300 men.

726
00:39:07,287 --> 00:39:08,777
But where do we bring
so many men from, boss?

727
00:39:08,856 --> 00:39:10,790
We might gather all those men.

728
00:39:10,858 --> 00:39:12,587
But boss, to tell 300
people about our plan

729
00:39:12,660 --> 00:39:14,821
..is fraught with danger.
- Correct.

730
00:39:15,496 --> 00:39:17,828
Even if one of those guys
turns out to be a police informer..

731
00:39:17,898 --> 00:39:19,331
..then we're finished.

732
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:20,594
Boss!
- What happened?

733
00:39:20,634 --> 00:39:23,569
l think this job is.. impossible.

734
00:39:24,938 --> 00:39:27,771
There's no such word as
'impossible' in my dictionary.

735
00:39:27,841 --> 00:39:29,331
Don't you know that? Get lost!
Get out of here.

736
00:39:29,410 --> 00:39:31,241
Boss, it's in my dictionary.
Want it?

737
00:39:31,311 --> 00:39:32,471
Yes, get it. Get your dictionary.

738
00:39:32,513 --> 00:39:33,707
Boss!
- What happened?

739
00:39:33,781 --> 00:39:34,839
Boss, come out.

740
00:39:35,482 --> 00:39:38,383
Why are you shouting?
Why are you shouting?

741
00:39:38,452 --> 00:39:40,545
You're shouting, boss.
Look, that same hero.

742
00:39:40,621 --> 00:39:42,350
'ls there any award you
haven't won in lndia?'

743
00:39:42,423 --> 00:39:44,323
'Which award are you
eyeing this time?'

744
00:39:45,025 --> 00:39:47,323
'Oscar!
- Oscar?'

745
00:39:47,394 --> 00:39:48,520
'Yes.'

746
00:39:48,595 --> 00:39:50,961
'Dumbdog Millionaire
was offered to me first.'

747
00:39:51,699 --> 00:39:54,998
'But due to my secretary
Bunty's foolishness..'

748
00:39:55,269 --> 00:39:56,759
'..that role slipped
out of my hands.'

749
00:39:56,837 --> 00:39:57,895
'Sir, it hurts.'

750
00:39:58,038 --> 00:40:02,031
'But let me assure you
that Aatish Kapoor..'

751
00:40:02,276 --> 00:40:04,767
'..will win the Oscar next
year and bring it back to lndia.'

752
00:40:05,412 --> 00:40:07,812
'l want to do an Oscar
winning film.'

