1022
00:52:52,011 --> 00:52:53,638
Bring it quickly.
- Boss, the lights are 500 volts.

1023
00:52:53,713 --> 00:52:55,510
Do one thing. Tell the
sun to come on this side.

1024
00:52:55,548 --> 00:52:56,674
Sun, shift! Shift!

1025
00:52:56,749 --> 00:52:57,943
Bring me a camera!

1026
00:52:58,351 --> 00:53:00,319
Boss! Boss, big camera.

1027
00:53:00,386 --> 00:53:01,580
Very good. Do one thing.

1028
00:53:01,654 --> 00:53:03,451
Tell some women to lie
in the fields. Quickly.

1029
00:53:03,490 --> 00:53:05,822
Women, lie down!
Women! Women, lie down.

1030
00:53:05,892 --> 00:53:07,291
Sir, the sun doesn't budge.

1031
00:53:07,360 --> 00:53:09,521
lf the sun doesn't budge,
then do one thing.

1032
00:53:09,596 --> 00:53:10,893
Bribe it and tell it
to come on this side.

1033
00:53:10,964 --> 00:53:12,864
Okay. Sun, here's some money.

1034
00:53:12,966 --> 00:53:15,799
Boss, four women beat me up.

1035
00:53:16,002 --> 00:53:18,402
So you lie down
in the fields. Ready.

1036
00:53:18,671 --> 00:53:20,866
Somebody tell me what's going on.

1037
00:53:20,940 --> 00:53:22,430
Son, what are you doing?

1038
00:53:22,509 --> 00:53:23,942
Shooting. Shooting.

1039
00:53:24,010 --> 00:53:25,477
Shooting the animals?

1040
00:53:25,678 --> 00:53:26,804
Chinkara (lndian Gazelle)?
Black Buck?

1041
00:53:26,880 --> 00:53:29,906
l'm shooting for a film here.
l'm making a film.

1042
00:53:30,283 --> 00:53:31,580
Cinema, okay? Cinema.

1043
00:53:31,651 --> 00:53:33,414
Film shooting?
- Cinema?

1044
00:53:33,486 --> 00:53:35,977
Come on. Come on.

1045
00:53:36,055 --> 00:53:38,489
Shooting? Film shooting?

1046
00:53:38,791 --> 00:53:40,691
Gullu! Sattu! Aunty!

1047
00:53:40,760 --> 00:53:43,490
There's a film shooting
going on in our village.

1048
00:53:43,530 --> 00:53:45,589
Come on, everybody.

1049
00:53:50,637 --> 00:53:52,298
Grandpa, where are you going?

1050
00:53:52,372 --> 00:53:53,430
To watch the film shooting.

1051
00:53:53,506 --> 00:53:54,564
l'm also coming.

1052
00:53:54,641 --> 00:53:56,973
There's a film shooting
going on. Come on. Film shooting!

1053
00:53:57,410 --> 00:54:00,641
Shooting! Shooting! Yes!

1054
00:54:02,815 --> 00:54:04,578
Listen.
- Stop.

1055
00:54:04,651 --> 00:54:06,482
Where are you going?

1056
00:54:06,519 --> 00:54:08,612
Wait. l'm also coming
to watch the film shoot.

1057
00:54:16,029 --> 00:54:17,826
Move side. Move side.

1058
00:54:18,031 --> 00:54:20,022
Alright. Alright.

1059
00:54:20,300 --> 00:54:22,268
You too can watch it..

1060
00:54:22,335 --> 00:54:24,803
Move aside. Have you gone mad?

1061
00:54:25,738 --> 00:54:27,672
Hand is up!

1062
00:54:30,843 --> 00:54:32,834
lnspector Dhurinder.

1063
00:54:34,380 --> 00:54:36,405
l'm in charge of the
police station here.

1064
00:54:36,883 --> 00:54:41,582
Can l see your..
What do you call it? Permit.

1065
00:54:41,788 --> 00:54:43,278
Can l see your permit to shoot here?

1066
00:54:51,030 --> 00:54:52,691
Amazing.

1067
00:54:52,765 --> 00:54:54,323
Heard his voice?
- Yes.

1068
00:54:54,400 --> 00:54:55,958
Did you hear the inspector's voice?

1069
00:54:56,436 --> 00:55:00,497
Boss, l say let's
give him that main role.

1070
00:55:00,573 --> 00:55:03,303
Boss, let's give him the role of
the milkman. He looks like one.

1071
00:55:03,376 --> 00:55:04,741
No. No. Not the milkman's.

1072
00:55:04,811 --> 00:55:05,869
Let's change the role of the
milkman to that of an inspector.

1073
00:55:05,945 --> 00:55:07,242
Yes. Yes.

1074
00:55:07,313 --> 00:55:09,440
ls that.. is that possible?
- Of course. lt's possible.

1075
00:55:09,716 --> 00:55:12,651
But why would you change the
story of your film for me?

1076
00:55:12,719 --> 00:55:13,913
What's the need?

1077
00:55:13,987 --> 00:55:15,579
Who am l?
- The director.

1078
00:55:15,655 --> 00:55:17,452
So l can surely do that.

1079
00:55:17,724 --> 00:55:19,385
But will l be able to do it, sir?

1080
00:55:20,960 --> 00:55:22,757
Look, Dharmesh.
- Dharmesh?

1081
00:55:22,996 --> 00:55:26,955
ln this show business, either
you have it in you, or you don't.

1082
00:55:27,934 --> 00:55:29,629
And Dharmesh..
can l call you Dharmesh?

1083
00:55:29,702 --> 00:55:31,533
But Dhurinder is..
- All right, Dharmendra.

1084
00:55:32,038 --> 00:55:33,562
You have it in you.

1085
00:55:33,640 --> 00:55:34,800
What? What?

1086
00:55:34,874 --> 00:55:35,966
Oomph factor.

1087
00:55:36,042 --> 00:55:38,670
lt's a children's film. X-Factor.
- X-Factor.

1088
00:55:38,745 --> 00:55:43,978
You have that X-Factor.
And l want it. l want it.

1089
00:55:44,050 --> 00:55:47,417
X-Factor?
- No. l want the shooting permit.

1090
00:55:47,487 --> 00:55:48,681
Don't worry.

1091
00:55:48,755 --> 00:55:50,518
Just prepare for the film shoot.

1092
00:55:50,590 --> 00:55:52,785
l'll find a workaround
for the permit.

1093
00:55:53,459 --> 00:55:54,824
Heard that voice? Heard his voice?

1094
00:55:54,894 --> 00:55:56,418
He has been blessed
with a wonderful voice.

1095
00:55:56,496 --> 00:55:58,327
Go away. Sir, you're too much.

1096
00:55:58,398 --> 00:56:00,491
l stole the rascal's gun.

1097
00:56:00,566 --> 00:56:02,932
Give me a role.
- Give me a role as well.

1098
00:56:02,969 --> 00:56:04,732
Yes. Yes. Okay. Okay.

1099
00:56:04,804 --> 00:56:06,965
Alright. Alright.

1100
00:56:08,708 --> 00:56:10,801
Okay. Listen.
Listen. Listen carefully.

1101
00:56:10,877 --> 00:56:12,674
Listen to me very carefully.

1102
00:56:13,279 --> 00:56:17,841
All of you will get a role
in my next film. - Great.

1103
00:56:17,917 --> 00:56:19,248
Great.
- Clap.

1104
00:56:19,318 --> 00:56:22,583
The film will be shot after a week.

1105
00:56:22,789 --> 00:56:25,019
Till then all of you
make preparations.

1106
00:56:25,491 --> 00:56:26,651
What preparations, sir?

1107
00:56:27,660 --> 00:56:29,560
Yes, what preparations?
Good question.

1108
00:56:32,732 --> 00:56:38,466
All of you will have to get six
packs like these two. - Six packs?

1109
00:56:38,838 --> 00:56:41,329
Okay. We're leaving now.

1110
00:56:41,474 --> 00:56:42,771
See you next week.

1111
00:56:43,042 --> 00:56:48,344
Okay. Bye. Move. Move.
- l got it.

1112
00:56:50,750 --> 00:56:52,843
Someone get me down at least now.

1113
00:56:53,286 --> 00:56:54,685
Director!

1114
00:56:55,555 --> 00:56:58,524
'And the Oscar goes to Anil
Kapoor for Dumbdog Millionaire.'

1115
00:57:03,663 --> 00:57:06,928
Don't worry.

1116
00:57:07,300 --> 00:57:09,530
My hero is like your son.

1117
00:57:09,702 --> 00:57:11,363
Just send the cheque.

1118
00:57:11,637 --> 00:57:14,003
When are you visiting
Mother Goddess?

1119
00:57:14,273 --> 00:57:15,763
Darn it.
- Yes.

1120
00:57:16,642 --> 00:57:18,303
You rascal..

1121
00:57:18,878 --> 00:57:20,709
This is all because of you.

1122
00:57:21,647 --> 00:57:24,548
lnstead of him, l'd have
been in Hollywood today.

1123
00:57:25,852 --> 00:57:29,015
Only if you had told me
about Danny Toyle's call.

1124
00:57:29,322 --> 00:57:31,847
How could l know that
Toyle was Hollywood's Danny?

1125
00:57:32,024 --> 00:57:34,015
He said his name was Danny.

1126
00:57:34,293 --> 00:57:36,454
l thought he's Danny Denzongpa.
l drove him away.

1127
00:57:36,496 --> 00:57:37,793
Bunty!

1128
00:57:37,864 --> 00:57:39,491
The phone is ringing.

1129
00:57:39,532 --> 00:57:42,695
Sir. - Yes, security. Who is it?
- Someone called Manoj is here.

1130
00:57:43,269 --> 00:57:44,896
Aatish, have you
called anyone called Manoj?

1131
00:57:45,905 --> 00:57:47,463
Ask him his full name.

1132
00:57:47,673 --> 00:57:48,765
What's his full name?

1133
00:57:48,841 --> 00:57:50,934
Manoj Ramalan from Hollywood.
- l see.

1134
00:57:51,010 --> 00:57:52,705
Manoj Ramalan from Hollywood.

1135
00:57:54,847 --> 00:57:56,439
Manoj Ramalan?

1136
00:57:56,816 --> 00:57:58,909
Director of 'Sixth
Sense' has come to meet me?

1137
00:57:59,786 --> 00:58:01,219
Call him inside, you idiot.

1138
00:58:01,287 --> 00:58:02,982
Send him in.
- Yes, sir.

1139
00:58:03,790 --> 00:58:08,523
l'm sure he's brought
a Hollywood offer. Yes! Yes!

1140
00:58:09,529 --> 00:58:11,497
Aatish, looks like your dream of..

1141
00:58:11,497 --> 00:58:13,658
..going to Hollywood
will be fulfilled.

1142
00:58:13,933 --> 00:58:15,491
God is great.

1143
00:58:15,735 --> 00:58:17,464
Thank God l was here.

1144
00:58:17,837 --> 00:58:19,737
Otherwise, you'd have
mistaken him for Manoj Bajpai..

1145
00:58:19,806 --> 00:58:21,273
..and driven him away.

1146
00:58:21,340 --> 00:58:22,773
l'm not such a fool, sir.

1147
00:58:22,842 --> 00:58:25,868
Bring him in. l'll get ready.
- Yes, absolutely.

1148
00:58:31,417 --> 00:58:33,351
Who the hell are you? Who are you?

1149
00:58:33,586 --> 00:58:35,281
l'm Bunty Baweja.

1150
00:58:35,888 --> 00:58:37,617
There must be some reason.
- What?

1151
00:58:37,690 --> 00:58:39,783
You just said Bunty
'Be-waja' (without reason).

1152
00:58:40,326 --> 00:58:43,420
Bunty Baweja.
l'm Mr. Aatish's secretary.

1153
00:58:43,496 --> 00:58:45,555
A servant.

1154
00:58:46,666 --> 00:58:48,031
You stink. Get out.

1155
00:58:48,267 --> 00:58:50,633
Where are you going?
Just tell me who you are.

1156
00:58:50,736 --> 00:58:53,967
l'm Manoj Ramalan, international
film director from Hollywood.

1157
00:58:54,040 --> 00:58:55,371
Touchwood.

1158
00:58:55,441 --> 00:58:57,739
No. No. You can't be Manoj Ramalan.

1159
00:58:57,910 --> 00:59:00,504
l've seen his photographs.
He's quiet.. - Dark.

1160
00:59:00,713 --> 00:59:02,840
He's dark. l know that.
- Yes. Yes.

1161
00:59:02,915 --> 00:59:04,212
Listen, servant.

1162
00:59:04,283 --> 00:59:06,478
The person whose
pictures you've seen..

1163
00:59:06,552 --> 00:59:10,215
..is actually my younger
brother Manoj Night Ramalan.

1164
00:59:11,490 --> 00:59:15,517
And l'm Manoj Day Ramalan.

1165
00:59:16,762 --> 00:59:19,390
My brother was born during
the night.

1166
00:59:19,532 --> 00:59:21,397
That's why he's dark.

1167
00:59:23,236 --> 00:59:26,364
And l was born during
the day. That's why l'm..

1168
00:59:26,439 --> 00:59:27,838
That's why l'm..
- Fair.

1169
00:59:30,376 --> 00:59:31,434
Okay.

1170
00:59:31,777 --> 00:59:34,245
Aatish! Where is Aatish? Aatish!

1171
00:59:34,313 --> 00:59:35,803
Search! Search! Aatish! Aatish!

1172
00:59:35,882 --> 00:59:38,783
Aatish! Aatish! Come on, fast.

1173
00:59:38,851 --> 00:59:41,251
Dear Aatish.
- Aatish.

1174
00:59:41,320 --> 00:59:43,754
Dear Aatish.
- Aatish.

1175
00:59:48,461 --> 00:59:49,723
There he is.

1176
00:59:50,029 --> 00:59:51,553
My superstar.

1177
00:59:53,699 --> 00:59:55,792
My Oscar!

1178
00:59:57,370 --> 00:59:58,428
Oscar?

1179
00:59:58,504 --> 01:00:00,369
Yes. Oscar.

1180
01:00:01,507 --> 01:00:03,372
l've made many films in Hollywood..

1181
01:00:03,442 --> 01:00:06,741
..but l'm going to make a film
about lndia for the first time.

1182
01:00:07,513 --> 01:00:13,543
lndia's poverty and
lndia's poor superstar.

1183
01:00:13,586 --> 01:00:14,780
Sir..

1184
01:00:15,788 --> 01:00:18,313
Perfect recipe for Oscar.

1185
01:00:20,026 --> 01:00:21,516
Sir.

1186
01:00:26,699 --> 01:00:28,758
Yes?
- May l speak to Manoj Ramalan?

1187
01:00:29,068 --> 01:00:30,729
Hold on.

1188
01:00:31,337 --> 01:00:32,929
Boss, Amir (rich).

1189
01:00:33,472 --> 01:00:35,440
l got a poor guy.
l don't want a rich one.

1190
01:00:35,608 --> 01:00:39,408
Sir, Aamir Khan. That one?

1191
01:00:39,478 --> 01:00:40,809
Oh, these strugglers.

1192
01:00:40,880 --> 01:00:42,677
Tell him.. Okay, l'll tell him.

1193
01:00:42,915 --> 01:00:46,681
Aamir, l'm making this film
especially for the Oscars. Okay?

1194
01:00:46,752 --> 01:00:48,720
l need actors who look poor. Okay?

1195
01:00:48,788 --> 01:00:49,982
l don't want you. Bye.

1196
01:00:51,457 --> 01:00:53,823
Look, what a poor guy.
What a poor guy.

1197
01:00:54,026 --> 01:00:57,826
l've decided to make this film
with Aatish Kapoor in the lead.

1198
01:00:57,897 --> 01:00:58,955
Got it?

1199
01:00:59,865 --> 01:01:02,527
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

1200
01:01:02,969 --> 01:01:08,032
Film? Film? Darn it! What film?
l just don't get it.

1201
01:01:08,407 --> 01:01:11,001
Why is your servant shouting at me?

1202
01:01:11,610 --> 01:01:14,909
l'd rather take Aamir
than tolerate this man.

1203
01:01:14,981 --> 01:01:16,471
Call up Aamir.
- He's online.

1204
01:01:16,515 --> 01:01:18,039
No. No. Sir, not Aamir.
Please. Please.

1205
01:01:18,317 --> 01:01:19,648
Then say something to him.

1206
01:01:19,919 --> 01:01:23,548
Bunty, shout again at the director
and l'll pull your pants down.

1207
01:01:23,622 --> 01:01:25,385
Please, sir. Not my pants.

1208
01:01:25,458 --> 01:01:26,550
l just..

1209
01:01:26,692 --> 01:01:29,593
l just wanted to ask what
the story of the film is.

1210
01:01:29,862 --> 01:01:31,921
What crime have
l committed by asking that?

1211
01:01:33,799 --> 01:01:35,994
