They're oppressing
simple and innocent lndians.

1508
01:16:01,940 --> 01:16:03,237
No.

1509
01:16:03,308 --> 01:16:07,244
They've riddled lndia, our
motherland, with bullets.

1510
01:16:07,312 --> 01:16:08,802
Mother.
- Mother.

1511
01:16:08,847 --> 01:16:10,109
Yes.
- No!

1512
01:16:10,182 --> 01:16:14,585
They've even killed
our women and children.

1513
01:16:15,220 --> 01:16:16,949
No! No!

1514
01:16:17,022 --> 01:16:20,082
Take the shot. Boss, take the shot.
- Yes.

1515
01:16:20,158 --> 01:16:21,853
Action!

1516
01:16:44,316 --> 01:16:45,874
Aatish.

1517
01:17:14,112 --> 01:17:17,104
You British! Rascal!

1518
01:17:24,823 --> 01:17:26,620
You British! Rascal!

1519
01:17:26,758 --> 01:17:30,159
Where is the hard-earned
money of the poor lndians?

1520
01:17:30,295 --> 01:17:32,957
Tell me! Tell me!

1521
01:17:33,031 --> 01:17:35,329
Perhaps, he doesn't
understand Hindi.

1522
01:17:35,667 --> 01:17:36,861
Let me try.

1523
01:17:37,969 --> 01:17:39,630
You dirty dog!

1524
01:17:39,704 --> 01:17:44,300
Tell me. Where is the hard-earned
money of the poor lndians?

1525
01:17:44,576 --> 01:17:46,305
Tell me. Tell me. Speak!

1526
01:17:46,578 --> 01:17:48,136
Control. Control.

1527
01:17:48,313 --> 01:17:49,871
Get up.

1528
01:17:50,182 --> 01:17:52,173
Chew. Chew.

1529
01:17:52,717 --> 01:17:55,777
What will you poor
lndians do with the money?

1530
01:17:55,821 --> 01:17:58,813
Followers of non-violence.
You can't even buy guns.

1531
01:17:58,924 --> 01:18:01,620
You roam naked wearing
handmade cloth.

1532
01:18:02,694 --> 01:18:05,026
Hit the British officer.

1533
01:18:05,096 --> 01:18:06,188
How was that?

1534
01:18:06,331 --> 01:18:09,095
My naked hand on your naked cheek?

1535
01:18:09,167 --> 01:18:13,001
Very nice. l'll go get
the money now.

1536
01:18:14,573 --> 01:18:17,133
Wide shot. Wide shot. Wide shot.

1537
01:18:17,876 --> 01:18:19,104
Keep going. Keep going.

1538
01:18:19,177 --> 01:18:20,610
Start the camera.

1539
01:18:23,114 --> 01:18:24,911
Forgive me.
- Get out!

1540
01:18:35,126 --> 01:18:37,060
Will you fire a cannon at me?

1541
01:18:39,130 --> 01:18:41,928
Fire it at my chest
if you have the guts.

1542
01:18:42,033 --> 01:18:44,194
Boss, he's become insane. Stop him.

1543
01:18:44,269 --> 01:18:46,999
Fire it if you have the guts.

1544
01:18:47,072 --> 01:18:48,767
Boss, cut. Cut it.

1545
01:18:48,840 --> 01:18:50,603
Cut. Cut.

1546
01:18:50,675 --> 01:18:52,870
Fire! Fire!

1547
01:18:52,944 --> 01:18:56,971
Dyer, fire it if you
have any self-respect.

1548
01:18:57,048 --> 01:18:59,312
Cut!

1549
01:18:59,584 --> 01:19:01,176
Boss!

1550
01:19:04,556 --> 01:19:06,114
Cut!

1551
01:19:06,324 --> 01:19:08,758
Fire! Fire!

1552
01:19:09,294 --> 01:19:10,955
No.
- Cut!

1553
01:19:11,096 --> 01:19:14,065
Fire!

1554
01:19:14,132 --> 01:19:15,690
Water.

1555
01:19:15,967 --> 01:19:17,559
Cut!

1556
01:19:29,114 --> 01:19:30,240
Sorry, Day.

1557
01:19:30,315 --> 01:19:32,306
l just got into the character.

1558
01:19:32,951 --> 01:19:34,748
l thought you'd get
into the camera.

1559
01:19:34,819 --> 01:19:38,311
But what a performance.
What a performance.

1560
01:19:38,690 --> 01:19:40,055
Oscar award-winning performance.

1561
01:19:40,125 --> 01:19:41,183
And my performance?

1562
01:19:41,259 --> 01:19:42,954
You'll get a Rotary Club award.

1563
01:19:43,094 --> 01:19:44,891
Well, l'll go write my speech.

1564
01:19:44,963 --> 01:19:46,260
Go. Go on quickly.

1565
01:19:46,531 --> 01:19:47,623
Sir, l'll go change.

1566
01:19:47,699 --> 01:19:49,530
Yes, go change. Go dry yourself.

1567
01:19:49,601 --> 01:19:50,659
Listen to me.

1568
01:19:50,735 --> 01:19:52,134
Love you, sir. l love you.

1569
01:19:54,606 --> 01:19:55,698
He's crazy.

1570
01:19:55,774 --> 01:19:57,173
Excuse me, boss. Need to tell
you something important. - Tell me.

1571
01:19:57,242 --> 01:19:58,300
The film is over.

1572
01:19:58,577 --> 01:19:59,635
l'll slap you, okay?

1573
01:19:59,711 --> 01:20:01,235
The film won't get over
until we loot the goods.

1574
01:20:01,313 --> 01:20:02,610
No. No. Not that stuff.

1575
01:20:02,681 --> 01:20:04,012
The film that goes in the camera.

1576
01:20:04,649 --> 01:20:06,276
The negatives?
- Yes, we've run out of those.

1577
01:20:06,651 --> 01:20:08,050
The stock that
we stole from Mumbai..

1578
01:20:08,119 --> 01:20:10,144
l mean, boss,
the stock we brought..

1579
01:20:10,221 --> 01:20:11,916
We've run out of that. Boss,
l have an idea.

1580
01:20:11,990 --> 01:20:13,719
Let's shoot without the stock.
What would they know?

1581
01:20:13,792 --> 01:20:14,781
That's better.

1582
01:20:15,026 --> 01:20:16,084
No.

1583
01:20:16,194 --> 01:20:18,662
Aatish and Bunty have been in
the film industry for ten years.

1584
01:20:18,863 --> 01:20:20,558
We might handle Aatish.

1585
01:20:20,632 --> 01:20:22,031
But Bunty will understand
immediately.

1586
01:20:22,100 --> 01:20:23,192
Boss, what do we do then?

1587
01:20:23,268 --> 01:20:24,735
We'll have to bring
the stuff from the city.

1588
01:20:24,869 --> 01:20:26,131
We've also run out of money.

1589
01:20:26,271 --> 01:20:28,068
We have to shoot for
another five to six days.

1590
01:20:28,139 --> 01:20:29,800
So we'll need at least
Rs.500,000 to Rs.600,000.

1591
01:20:32,277 --> 01:20:33,335
What's that?

1592
01:20:33,612 --> 01:20:35,170
Boss, the keys to the bank.

1593
01:20:35,246 --> 01:20:37,840
The bank manager Santram
himself gave it to us.

1594
01:20:37,916 --> 01:20:39,144
What do you think, boss?

1595
01:20:39,284 --> 01:20:41,582
Wonderful suggestion. Well done.

1596
01:20:41,653 --> 01:20:43,177
Boss, what if something goes wrong?

1597
01:20:43,254 --> 01:20:45,586
lf you're not good looking,
you should say good things.

1598
01:20:46,091 --> 01:20:47,251
lt's Friday today.

1599
01:20:47,592 --> 01:20:48,889
The bank will be closed
for the next two days.

1600
01:20:48,994 --> 01:20:50,188
lt's a bank holiday on Monday.

1601
01:20:50,228 --> 01:20:51,661
We'll be robbing
the train on Tuesday.

1602
01:20:51,730 --> 01:20:52,788
The whole village will be there.

1603
01:20:52,864 --> 01:20:55,196
Nobody will know before Wednesday
that we've robbed the bank.

1604
01:20:55,266 --> 01:20:57,166
And we would've left
with the goods.

1605
01:20:57,569 --> 01:20:59,036
And we'd have been
relaxing somewhere.

1606
01:20:59,104 --> 01:21:00,298
Boss!
- Wonderful.

1607
01:21:00,572 --> 01:21:02,096
Enough. Enough.

1608
01:21:02,607 --> 01:21:04,165
God has been so kind to us, Nana..

1609
01:21:04,242 --> 01:21:06,870
..that this film crew came to
Dhuliya to shoot for their film.

1610
01:21:06,945 --> 01:21:09,846
That day is not too far, when
tourists will come to Dhuliya..

1611
01:21:09,914 --> 01:21:11,882
..on a holiday or on honeymoon.

1612
01:21:11,950 --> 01:21:16,785
Yes. And soon we'll
have good business.

1613
01:21:17,155 --> 01:21:18,884
Listen. Listen.

1614
01:21:19,090 --> 01:21:20,921
The film shoot that was
supposed to take place..

1615
01:21:20,992 --> 01:21:22,323
..will not happen now.

1616
01:21:22,594 --> 01:21:23,788
What?
- Yes.

1617
01:21:24,796 --> 01:21:27,321
Quietly. Quietly.
- What? Should l stop walking now?

1618
01:21:28,900 --> 01:21:30,629
Boss, looks like he's dead.

1619
01:21:30,735 --> 01:21:32,669
ls he your nephew? ''He's dead.''

1620
01:21:32,771 --> 01:21:34,033
Get in.

1621
01:21:34,072 --> 01:21:35,937
Come on. Quickly. Quickly.

1622
01:21:36,207 --> 01:21:39,574
You know what, Mummy? The hero
of the film is Aatish Kapoor.

1623
01:21:40,612 --> 01:21:41,806
But the main role is mine.

1624
01:21:41,880 --> 01:21:45,111
Do you know that l was a big
fan of Aatish Kapoor's father?

1625
01:21:45,650 --> 01:21:47,709
l'll also come for your film shoot.

1626
01:21:47,819 --> 01:21:49,753
After all, l'm the
director's mother.

1627
01:21:49,788 --> 01:21:51,187
Well, where is your
film shoot taking place?

1628
01:21:52,624 --> 01:21:55,593
Girls, where are we?
- Dhuliya.

1629
01:21:57,829 --> 01:22:00,696
Dhuliya.
- Dhuliya? l'll drop by over there.

1630
01:22:01,032 --> 01:22:03,262
ls the film shoot
going well? Take care. Bye.

1631
01:22:03,535 --> 01:22:06,095
Okay, Mummy. Bye.

1632
01:22:06,171 --> 01:22:08,002
My mother-in-low.

1633
01:22:08,073 --> 01:22:11,065
Listen, have any of
you seen the director?

1634
01:22:11,142 --> 01:22:12,666
Yes, l've seen him. l've seen him.

1635
01:22:12,811 --> 01:22:15,041
He and his three friends
have gone towards the bank.

1636
01:22:15,213 --> 01:22:17,204
Bank! Bank?

1637
01:22:17,716 --> 01:22:21,311
Close the door.
Our job is done. Come on.

1638
01:22:24,189 --> 01:22:27,249
Boss, looks like they've
found out about our plan.

1639
01:22:27,325 --> 01:22:28,656
What do we do now, boss?

1640
01:22:28,893 --> 01:22:30,918
There's only one thing you
can do in such a situation.

1641
01:22:30,995 --> 01:22:32,292
What?

1642
01:22:32,564 --> 01:22:33,758
Run!

1643
01:22:33,798 --> 01:22:35,925
Run! Run! Run!

1644
01:22:36,334 --> 01:22:37,926
Mummy.

1645
01:22:38,937 --> 01:22:40,495
Run!

1646
01:22:43,041 --> 01:22:44,736
Look. There's the director.
- Where?

1647
01:22:44,776 --> 01:22:46,607
They're going towards
the dark jungle.

1648
01:22:46,745 --> 01:22:48,679
Oh, God! Somebody stop them.

1649
01:22:48,747 --> 01:22:50,578
That is the jungle
of the Headless Ghost.

1650
01:22:50,648 --> 01:22:52,172
Will somebody stop him..

1651
01:22:52,250 --> 01:22:54,718
..or do l have to do
that as well? Come on.

1652
01:22:54,786 --> 01:22:56,185
Where are you going?

1653
01:22:56,221 --> 01:22:58,781
Director! Stop!

1654
01:22:58,857 --> 01:23:01,553
Director. Don't go that way.

1655
01:23:01,626 --> 01:23:05,653
Stop!
- lt will kill you!

1656
01:23:05,764 --> 01:23:07,698
Heard that? They will kill us. Run!

1657
01:23:07,799 --> 01:23:09,926
They will kill us.

1658
01:23:10,001 --> 01:23:11,628
Boss, run!

1659
01:23:11,703 --> 01:23:13,295
ldiots, stop.

1660
01:23:13,571 --> 01:23:15,937
Director, stop! Stop.
- Run!

1661
01:23:16,708 --> 01:23:19,700
l'll run faster than you.
ldiots. You never stop.

1662
01:23:19,878 --> 01:23:23,609
l'll not stop for you.
- Boss! - Run!

1663
01:23:25,550 --> 01:23:27,711
They're going deeper
into the woods.

1664
01:23:27,786 --> 01:23:29,083
But why aren't they stopping?

1665
01:23:29,154 --> 01:23:31,952
lnspector, you come with us as well.
- Yes, come on.

1666
01:23:33,057 --> 01:23:36,049
What's going on?
Why haven't you stopped them yet?

1667
01:23:36,094 --> 01:23:38,619
Our boys have gone
to the dark jungle.

1668
01:23:38,663 --> 01:23:40,255
For me, every jungle is dark.

1669
01:23:40,799 --> 01:23:42,664
Boss!
- Run!

1670
01:23:42,734 --> 01:23:43,962
Boss!

1671
01:23:53,812 --> 01:23:55,074
Boss!

1672
01:24:02,320 --> 01:24:04,151
Oh, God! Ghost!

1673
01:24:13,298 --> 01:24:14,765
Ghost!

1674
01:24:15,333 --> 01:24:16,994
Headless Ghost!

1675
01:24:17,101 --> 01:24:19,729
Ghost! Run! Ghost!

1676
01:24:26,845 --> 01:24:28,369
Headless ghost!

1677
01:24:29,247 --> 01:24:33,013
Ghost! Run! Don't stop! Run!

1678
01:24:33,084 --> 01:24:35,780
Run. Ghost!

1679
01:24:37,222 --> 01:24:39,156
''Tees Maar Khan.''

1680
01:24:39,824 --> 01:24:41,291
Run.

1681
01:24:41,559 --> 01:24:43,322
Where is boss going?

1682
01:24:43,728 --> 01:24:44,820
After the ghost.

1683
01:24:44,896 --> 01:24:45,988
Boss has gone crazy.

1684
01:24:46,064 --> 01:24:47,725
Run!
- Run!

1685
01:24:47,799 --> 01:24:49,323
Stop! Stop!
- What happened?

1686
01:24:49,601 --> 01:24:52,798
Look. The director is going
towards the ghost. - What?

1687
01:25:01,746 --> 01:25:04,010
Boss is in danger.
We should help him.

1688
01:25:04,082 --> 01:25:06,141
But that's a ghost over there.

1689
01:25:06,217 --> 01:25:07,582
That's exactly
why we should help him.

1690
01:25:07,652 --> 01:25:09,313
Had it been a human,
boss would've handled him.

1691
01:25:19,097 --> 01:25:21,827
The Director has gone to
fight the ghost for us.

1692
01:25:21,900 --> 01:25:23,891
We should lend him support.

1693
01:25:23,968 --> 01:25:25,367
He's right. He's right.

1694
01:25:25,803 --> 01:25:27,668
Attack!

1695
01:25:27,739 --> 01:25:30,299
Attack!

1696
01:25:39,183 --> 01:25:40,309
He ran away.

1697
01:25:42,053 --> 01:25:44,021
Attack!

1698
01:25:44,088 --> 01:25:46,056
Attack!

1699
01:25:54,933 --> 01:25:56,594
Attack!

1700
01:25:56,734 --> 01:25:57,928
Attack!

1701
01:25:58,002 --> 01:25:59,230
Easy.
- Boss.

1702
01:25:59,604 --> 01:26:00,798
Boss, what's happening?

1703
01:26:00,905 --> 01:26:02,031
How would boss know?

1704
01:26:06,611 --> 01:26:07,873
What's going on here?

1705
01:26:07,946 --> 01:26:09,709
Yes. What's going on here?

1706
01:26:09,781 --> 01:26:11,806
Catch them! Attack!

1707
01:26:11,849 --> 01:26:13,817
Attack!

1708
01:26:13,851 --> 01:26:15,011
Attack!

1709
01:26:15,086 --> 01:26:16,781
Are you crazy? Get out!

1710
01:26:30,601 --> 01:26:33,195
You.. What's going on here?
What's going on? Tell me.

1711
01:26:33,604 --> 01:26:35,834
Tell us. Speak. Speak.

1712
01:26:36,674 --> 01:26:39,370
Tell us. Speak.
Who are you? Speak.

1713
01:26:46,684 --> 01:26:48,777
What? This is Chenu's son.

1714
01:26:48,920 --> 01:26:50,785
He'd disappeared last year.

1715
01:26:51,222 --> 01:26:54,191
And we thought he
drowned in the river.

1716
01:26:54,625 --> 01:26:57,321
Gopal? My son Gopal.

1717
01:26:57,695 --> 01:26:59,060
Father! Father!

1718
01:26:59,130 --> 01:27:00,324
Come, my son.

1719
01:27:00,565 --> 01:27:02,897
Look. They both are Laxman's sons.

1720
01:27:02,967 --> 01:27:04,935
Munnu! My son Munnu.

1721
01:27:07,305 --> 01:27:08,829
Come here, headless ghost.

1722
01:27:08,906 --> 01:27:10,100
Remove his head!

1723
01:27:10,341 --> 01:27:11,706
Tell me. Tell me.

1724
01:27:11,776 --> 01:27:14,006
What's going on here?
Tell me. Tell me.

1725
01:27:14,345 --> 01:27:15,642
l'll tell you.

1726
01:27:17,115 --> 01:27:18,673
We grow marijuana here.

1727
01:27:19,751 --> 01:27:23,847
We abducted all these
kids from your village..

1728
01:27:23,921 --> 01:27:25,616
..so that they can work for us.

1729
01:27:25,790 --> 01:27:27,348
And we'd spread the
terror of the headless ghost..

1730
01:27:27,625 --> 01:27:32,085
..so that the villagers
wouldn't venture into this jungle.

1731
01:27:33,598 --> 01:27:38,228
Shame on us.
We couldn't do anything, Subedar.

1732
01:27:39,137 --> 01:27:41,264
Had it not been for our director..

1733
01:27:41,706 --> 01:27:43,799
''Tees Maar Khan.''

1734
01:27:54,786 --> 01:28:01,783
You risked your life for us
and faced such great danger.

1735
01:28:02,260 --> 01:28:10,133
We've never seen such
a brave person. - Yes.

1736
01:28:10,301 --> 01:28:14,067
We'll always be indebted to you.

1737
01:28:14,605 --> 01:28:17,005
But we can surely do our bit.

1738
01:28:18,342 --> 01:28:19,673
What's this?

1739
01:28:19,744 --> 01:28:20,836
No.

1740
01:28:20,912 --> 01:28:24,643
Santram told us that
you're in need of money.

1741
01:28:24,916 --> 01:28:28,716
So we've collected as
much as we can afford.

1742
01:28:28,886 --> 01:28:30,877
lt must be between
Rs.500,000 to Rs.600,000.

1743
01:28:30,955 --> 01:28:34,823
l hope it will be
useful for your film shoot.

1744
01:28:35,660 --> 01:28:37,150
As soon as the bank opens,
we'll arrange for more..

1745
01:28:37,228 --> 01:28:38,320
No. No.

1746
01:28:38,596 --> 01:28:40,564
This will do. Thank you.

1747
01:28:40,698 --> 01:28:45,135
You've done us a great
favour by accepting this money.

1748
01:28:45,303 --> 01:28:50,104
Complete your film. Don't
stop the film shoot. Thank you.

1749
01:28:50,775 --> 01:28:52,743
Let's go, friends.

1750
01:28:55,146 --> 01:28:59,242
Boss, we've cheated
these simple people.

1751
01:29:00,585 --> 01:29:03,782
We did something wrong, but
we'll also do something good.

1752
01:29:05,156 --> 01:29:07,624
Before leaving, we'll give them..

1753
01:29:08,059 --> 01:29:10,254
..something from our
share of the loot.

1754
01:29:11,062 --> 01:29:12,620
And the money we
robbed from them as well.

1755
01:29:12,697 --> 01:29:13,925
Really, boss?

1756
01:29:14,565 --> 01:29:16,055
The toothpaste that's
come out of the tube..

1757
01:29:16,134 --> 01:29:18,227
..and the commitment that
Tees Maar Khan has given..

1758
01:29:18,836 --> 01:29:20,326
..can never be taken back.

1759
01:29:20,838 --> 01:29:24,865
The Khan of Khans. Tees Maar Khan.

